{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847542296,"sessionID":"ses_2873ed6d6ffebx07opRS5b8lQ3","part":{"id":"prt_d78c14964001vmH1Qgt0lc1lvy","messageID":"msg_d78c1321c0011aRcJ9lJI7Y2hu","sessionID":"ses_2873ed6d6ffebx07opRS5b8lQ3","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"toolu_tool-7d389d27675d4cb6af4d803514cabb56","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/.sdd_prompt.md","description":"Explore workloadmanager module structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure, specifically focusing on:\n1. The pkg/workloadmanager module - its files, structure, and existing implementations\n2. Any existing sandbox-related code or GC mechanisms\n3. The API definitions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n4. Configuration patterns and controller patterns used in the project\n\nProvide a comprehensive overview of the current implementation that will inform the design of the Sandbox GC定时清理机制 feature.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2873eb683ffeGgdffYGXQ39Sq2 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\n# Comprehensive Overview of AgentCube Project Structure\n\nBased on my exploration of the agentcube project, here's a detailed analysis of the workloadmanager module structure and its implementation patterns:\n\n## 1. pkg/workloadmanager Module Structure\n\n### Directory Layout\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── api/                    # HTTP API types and response handlers\n│   ├── response.go         # API response utilities\n│   └── types.go            # Request/response type definitions\n├── auth/                   # Authentication and authorization\n│   └── k8s_auth.go         # Kubernetes token review integration\n├── client/                 # Kubernetes client wrapper\n│   └── k8s_client.go       # Dynamic client for K8s API operations\n├── config/                 # Configuration management\n│   └── config.go           # Server, Redis, K8s, Auth, Session configs\n├── controller/             # Business logic controllers\n│   ├── reconciler/         # K8s controller-runtime reconcilers\n│   │   ├── codeinterpreter.go\n│   │   ├── controller.go\n│   │   ├── errors.go\n│   │   ├── finalizers.go\n│   │   ├── metrics.go\n│   │   ├── predicates.go\n│   │   └── status.go\n│   └── sandbox.go          # Sandbox lifecycle controller\n├── handler/                # HTTP request handlers\n│   ├── handler.go          # Main handler interface\n│   └── sandbox.go          # Sandbox deletion handler\n├── middleware/             # HTTP middleware\n│   └── middleware.go       # Recovery, logging, CORS\n├── server/                 # HTTP server setup\n│   └── server.go           # Server initialization and lifecycle\n├── types/                  # Type definitions\n│   └── sandbox_types.go    # Sandbox cleanup types\n├── garbage_collector.go    # Garbage collection implementation\n├── defaults.go             # Default constants and values\n└── design.md               # Comprehensive design document\n```\n\n**Total: 28 Go files** across 12 subdirectories\n\n## 2. Existing Sandbox-Related Code and GC Mechanisms\n\n### GarbageCollector Implementation (`garbage_collector.go`)\n\nThe project already has a **fully implemented** GarbageCollector with the following features:\n\n**Core Structure:**\n```go\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    dynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n    storeClient   store.Store\n    interval      time.Duration\n    ctx           context.Context\n    cancel        context.CancelFunc\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `NewGarbageCollector()` - Constructor accepting dynamic client, store, and interval\n- `Start()` - Starts the GC loop in a goroutine\n- `Stop()` - Gracefully stops the GC\n- `gcLoop()` - Main ticker-based loop (runs every 15 seconds by default)\n- `tick()` - Single cleanup iteration with timeout\n- `deleteSandbox()` - Deletes sandbox CR and cleans up store\n- `recordAudit()` - Logs cleanup operations\n\n**Supported GVRs:**\n- `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox`\n- `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/SandboxClaim`\n\n**Cleanup Triggers:**\n1. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes with `LastActivityAt < now - 15m`\n2. **Expired**: Sandboxes with `ExpiresAt < now`\n3. **Manual**: Explicit deletion requests\n\n**Default Constants:**\n```go\nconst (\n    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n    GCInterval                = 15 * time.Second\n    GCSingleTickTimeout       = 2 * time.Minute\n    DeleteTimeout             = 30 * time.Second\n)\n```\n\n### Store Interface (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n\nThe Store interface provides GC-related methods:\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    // ... other methods\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n- Redis-backed storage using `go-redis/v9`\n- Session keys pattern: `session:{sessionID}`\n- TTL automatically set based on `ExpiresAt`\n- Batch size limit: 16 sandboxes per GC tick\n\n### Cleanup Types (`types/sandbox_types.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxCleanupReason string\n\nconst (\n    CleanupReasonManual      SandboxCleanupReason = \"manual\"\n    CleanupReasonIdleTimeout SandboxCleanupReason = \"idle_timeout\"\n    CleanupReasonExpired     SandboxCleanupReason = \"expired\"\n)\n\ntype CleanupAuditEntry struct {\n    SessionID    string               `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID    string               `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    Namespace    string               `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Reason       SandboxCleanupReason `json:\"reason\"`\n    DeletedAt    time.Time            `json:\"deletedAt\"`\n    Success      bool                 `json:\"success\"`\n    ErrorMessage string               `json:\"errorMessage,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n## 3. API Definitions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n\n### AgentRuntime CRD (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta\n    metav1.ObjectMeta\n    \n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    PodTemplate       *SandboxTemplate     `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n    SessionTimeout    *metav1.Duration     `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration    `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    Metadata *SandboxMetadata `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec     SandboxPodSpec  `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Default Values:**\n- `SessionTimeout`: 15m\n- `MaxSessionDuration`: 8h\n\n### CodeInterpreter CRD\n\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta\n    metav1.ObjectMeta\n    \n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Image           string                     `json:\"image\"`\n    Runtime         string                     `json:\"runtime,omitempty\"`\n    Timeout         *metav1.Duration           `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n    Resources       *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n    Env             []SandboxEnvVar            `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n    EnabledPackages []string                   `json:\"enabledPackages,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Default Values:**\n- `Runtime`: \"python\"\n- `Timeout`: 5m\n\n### HTTP API Endpoints\n\n**Sandbox Creation:**\n```\nPOST /v1/agent-runtime\nPOST /v1/code-interpreter\n\nRequest: {\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime|CodeInterpreter\",\n  \"name\": \"runtime-name\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\"\n}\n\nResponse: {\n  \"sessionId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-uuid\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"runtime-name-xxxxx\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [...],\n  \"createdAt\": \"timestamp\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"timestamp\"\n}\n```\n\n**Session Management:**\n```\nGET    /v1/sessions/:sessionId\nDELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\nDELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId\n```\n\n## 4. Configuration and Controller Patterns\n\n### Configuration Pattern (`config/config.go`)\n\n**Hierarchical Configuration Structure:**\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Server   ServerConfig\n    Redis    RedisConfig\n    K8s      K8sConfig\n    Auth     AuthConfig\n    Session  SessionConfig\n}\n\ntype SessionConfig struct {\n    DefaultTimeout    time.Duration  // Default: 15m\n    MaxDuration       time.Duration  // Default: 8h\n    CleanupInterval   time.Duration  // Default: 15s\n    KeepAliveEnabled  bool           // Default: true\n    KeepAliveInterval time.Duration  // Default: 5m\n    RenewalWindow     time.Duration  // Default: 2m\n}\n```\n\n**Default Configuration Provider:**\n- `DefaultConfig()` returns fully initialized config with safe defaults\n- Uses environment variable overrides\n- Supports both JSON/YAML config files and environment variables\n\n### Controller Pattern\n\n**1. Business Logic Controller (`controller/sandbox.go`):**\n```go\ntype Controller interface {\n    CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *api.CreateSandboxRequest) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error)\n    CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox(ctx context.Context, req *api.CreateSandboxRequest) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error)\n    GetSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*api.GetSessionResponse, error)\n    DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*api.DeleteSessionResponse, error)\n}\n\ntype SandboxController struct {\n    k8sClient client.Client\n    store     store.Store\n}\n```\n\n**Responsibilities:**\n- Sandbox creation workflow (CR creation, Pod IP waiting, store updates)\n- Session lifecycle management\n- Integration with K8s API and Store\n\n**2. K8s Reconciler Pattern (`controller/reconciler/controller.go`):**\n```go\ntype ControllerConfig struct {\n    RequeueAfter            time.Duration  // Default: 10s\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int            // Default: 2\n    EnableLeaderElection    bool           // Default: true\n    MetricsAddr             string         // Default: \":8080\"\n}\n\nfunc NewControllerManager(cfg *rest.Config, controllerCfg *ControllerConfig) (ctrl.Manager, error)\nfunc SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager, cli client.Client, cfg *ControllerConfig) error\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Uses `controller-runtime` framework\n- Leader election enabled by default\n- Configurable concurrency and requeue timing\n- Separate reconcilers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n\n**3. HTTP Handler Pattern (`handler/handler.go`):**\n```go\ntype Handler struct {\n    controller *controller.SandboxController\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(c *gin.Context)\nfunc (h *Handler) CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox(c *gin.Context)\nfunc (h *Handler) GetSession(c *gin.Context)\nfunc (h *Handler) Health(c *gin.Context)\n```\n\n**Middleware Chain:**\n1. Recovery Middleware (panic handling)\n2. Logging Middleware (request/response logging)\n3. CORS Middleware (cross-origin support)\n\n### Server Lifecycle Pattern (`server/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config           *config.Config\n    router           *gin.Engine\n    server           *http.Server\n    k8sClient        *client.K8sClient\n    store            store.Store\n    controller       *controller.SandboxController\n    garbageCollector *workloadmanager.GarbageCollector\n    wg               sync.WaitGroup\n    ctx              context.Context\n    cancel           context.CancelFunc\n}\n\nfunc NewServer(cfg *config.Config) (*Server, error)\nfunc (s *Server) Start() error\nfunc (s *Server) Stop() error\n```\n\n**Startup Sequence:**\n1. Initialize K8s client (in-cluster config)\n2. Create Redis store connection\n3. Initialize controller and handlers\n4. Setup Gin router with middleware\n5. Register API routes\n6. Start GarbageCollector\n7. Start HTTP server\n\n**Shutdown Sequence:**\n1. Cancel context\n2. Shutdown HTTP server gracefully\n3. Stop GarbageCollector\n4. Wait for goroutines\n5. Close store connections\n\n## Key Design Insights for Sandbox GC Feature\n\n### 1. **Already Implemented**: The GarbageCollector is fully functional with:\n   - Ticker-based periodic cleanup (15s interval)\n   - Dual cleanup triggers (idle timeout + TTL expiry)\n   - Batch processing (16 items per tick)\n   - Audit logging with success/failure tracking\n   - Graceful shutdown support\n\n### 2. **Integration Points**:\n   - Store interface provides GC-specific query methods\n   - Server lifecycle manages GC start/stop\n   - Handler provides manual deletion endpoint\n   - Configuration allows tuning intervals\n\n### 3. **Patterns Used**:\n   - **Dependency Injection**: All components accept dependencies via constructors\n   - **Interface-Based Design**: Clear separation between interface and implementation\n   - **Context Propagation**: Context passed through all layers for cancellation\n   - **Graceful Shutdown**: Proper cleanup via context cancellation and WaitGroups\n   - **Default Configuration**: Sensible defaults with override capability\n   - **Structured Logging**: klog/v2 with consistent field names\n\n### 4. **Areas for Enhancement** (if needed for AR-008):\n   - Metrics/monitoring integration for GC operations\n   - Configurable batch size and timeout values\n   - Per-runtime idle timeout support (currently global)\n   - Dry-run mode for testing\n   - Resource quota-aware cleanup prioritization\n\nThe project demonstrates mature software engineering practices with clear separation of concerns, comprehensive type safety, and production-ready lifecycle management.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2873eb683ffeGgdffYGXQ39Sq2","model":{"modelID":"glm-4.7","providerID":"bailian-coding-plan"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore workloadmanager module structure","time":{"start":1775847426426,"end":1775847542292}}}}
